==================================================
SYNC FLOW
==================================================

1. :JudgeSync in Neovim → POST /local/sync
2. local-agent reads ./registry/index.json
3. Finds "providers/leetcode.json" → loads 25 ProblemManifest entries
4. POSTs to api-server POST /api/registry/sync
5. api-server upserts each problem (ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE)
6. api-server saves new registry_versions row
7. local-agent returns {synced: true, problems: 25, version: "1.0.0"}
8. Plugin shows: "Registry synced: 25 problems (version 1.0.0)"

curl example:
  curl -X POST http://localhost:7070/local/sync -d '{}'
  # Response: {"message":"Registry synced: 25 problems (version 1.0.0)","problems":25,"synced":true,"version":"1.0.0"}

  curl http://localhost:8080/api/registry/version
  # Response: {"synced_at":"...","version":"1.0.0"}

